/.quarto/
/_site/
.Rproj.user
.Rhistory
.RData
.DS_Store
# NOTE: do NOT ignore _freeze/ or renv.lock — they ARE the reproducibility.
renv/library/
renv/staging/

# knitr per-chunk caches (cache: true). Local build accelerator only —
# _freeze/ is the committed reproducibility record, NOT these.
**/*_cache/

# Quarto/knitr render leakage. A website project's output belongs in
# _site/ only; these appear when a page is rendered outside project mode.
# (assets/figures/ IS tracked content — pre-rendered figures — so it is
#  deliberately NOT matched here.)
**/*_files/
/figure/
/site_libs/
/posts/*-listing.json
/posts/*.feed*
/index.html
/guides/**/*.html
/theory/**/*.html
/contributing/**/*.html
/posts/**/*.html

# knitr render intermediates. Quarto knits .qmd -> .rmarkdown -> .knit.md and
# deletes these on success; a crashed/interrupted render leaves them behind.
# On the next full `quarto render` they get globbed in as phantom input files
# (e.g. "guides/example-analysis.rmarkdown" -> NotFound) and abort the build.
**/*.rmarkdown
**/*.knit.md

# CI scratch
targets.txt
drift-report.md

**/*.quarto_ipynb
